The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Income hike for village heads
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Income hike for village heads
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Dec. 12: Keeping the rural vote bank in view, chief minister Naveen Patnaik today announced a hike in monthly honorarium of sarpanch and panchayat samiti members.        
	The monthly honorarium of sarpanch will be hiked from Rs 600 to Rs 1,000 and that of pachayat samiti members from Rs 500 to Rs 1,000, Naveen said, adding that such hikes for other panchayati raj representatives would be decided later. There are more than 1 lakh elected panchayati raj representatives in the state.        
	The announcement was made at a rally of elected panchayati raj representatives in front of the Assembly today.                                                                                                                                                           
